  hook:"In 2023, the FDA approved the first CRISPR-based therapy — Casgevy — curing sickle cell disease by editing a patient's own DNA. A disease that afflicted millions, caused excruciating pain crises, and shortened lifespans by 20+ years can now be CURED by precisely changing a few letters in the patient's genetic code. India has ~20 million sickle cell carriers and 1.5 million patients — predominantly in tribal populations of central India. CRISPR (Clustered Regularly Interspaced Short Palindromic Repeats) is a molecular tool that lets scientists cut DNA at any precise location, delete faulty genes, insert corrected ones, or turn genes on and off — essentially a 'find-and-replace' for the code of life. How does a defense mechanism borrowed from bacteria enable us to rewrite the genome?",
